    <p>Wild Rice presents its award-win­ning, gen­der-bend­ing pro­duc­tion of Os­car Wilde’s The Im­por­tance Of Be­ing Earnest. Di­rec­tor Glen Goei casts an all-male en­sem­ble, in­clud­ing Ivan Heng, Hos­san Leong and Chua En­lai. For a small con­tri­bu­tion of US$10 (S$13.90), you can en­joy the pro­duc­tion at home for 48 hours.</p>
    <p>The pro­ceeds help con­trib­ute to the theatre com­pany’s sur­vival and pro­tect the liveli­hoods of its staff. On de­mand via Vimeo</p>
    <p>Till Aug 30</p>
    <p>US$10 (S$13.90) bit.ly/31cTyg1</p>
    <p>The Per­anakan As­so­ci­a­tion Sin­ga­pore Presents Bibiks Be­hind Bars, Kena Again!</p>
    <p>This is a screen­ing of an orig­i­nal mu­si­cal first staged in 2015 at</p>
    <p>The Per­anakan Arts Fes­ti­val and com­mis­sioned by the Per­anakan As­so­ci­a­tion. The rau­cous and hi­lar­i­ous mu­si­cal tells the lives of vi­va­cious, fun-lov­ing, and cherki- and mahjong-mad bibiks in Joo Chiat.</p>
    <p>The screen­ing cel­e­brates the as­so­ci­a­tion’s 120th an­niver­sary.</p>
    <p>Per­anakan As­so­ci­a­tion’s Face­book page Till Sept 19</p>
    <p>Free, but view­ers can make a do­na­tion at per­anakan.org.sg/do­nate</p>
    <p>bit.ly/31e5oGC</p>


